abstract: Democrats held their final debate before the South Carolina presidential primary and the critical Super Tuesday contests that follow three days later.
snippet: Democrats held their final debate before the South Carolina presidential primary and the critical Super Tuesday contests that follow three days later.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democrats held their final debate before the South Carolina presidential primary and the critical Super Tuesday contests that follow three days later.
headline_main: Debate Takeaways: Bernie Bruised but Not Broken
headline_print_headline: Debate Takeaways: Bernie Bruised but Not Broken

abstract: Pressured by Joe Biden about his past support for a law that gave gun manufacturers immunity in wrongful death suits, Bernie Sanders acknowledged a “bad vote.”

headline_main: Bernie Sanders Confronts ‘Bad Vote’ on Guns

abstract: The Democratic front-runner faced criticism about his past support for a 2005 law that shields the firearms industry from wrongful death lawsuits.
snippet: The Democratic front-runner faced criticism about his past support for a 2005 law that shields the firearms industry from wrongful death lawsuits.
lead_paragraph: Blocks from where nine people were killed in a mass shooting at a historic Charleston, S.C., black church in 2015, the Democratic presidential front-runner, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, was confronted on Tuesday night about his past support for a law that gave immunity to gun manufacturers in wrongful death lawsuits.

abstract: In a messy Democratic forum, Bernie Sanders, the emerging front-runner, faced his most serious test so far. Michael R. Bloomberg also drew withering criticism.
snippet: In a messy Democratic forum, Bernie Sanders, the emerging front-runner, faced his most serious test so far. Michael R. Bloomberg also drew withering criticism.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — The Democratic presidential candidates delivered a barrage of criticism against their party’s emerging front-runner, Senator Bernie Sanders, at a debate on Tuesday night, casting him as a divisive figure with unrealistic ideas, even as they continued to batter Michael R. Bloomberg for his extreme wealth, his record on policing and his alleged behavior toward women.

abstract: An effort to encourage conservatives to participate in the state’s open primary for Democrats is meant to show the process’s flaws. Chaos, organizers said, would be a side benefit.
snippet: An effort to encourage conservatives to participate in the state’s open primary for Democrats is meant to show the process’s flaws. Chaos, organizers said, would be a side benefit.
lead_paragraph: By canceling this year’s presidential primary, the Republican Party of South Carolina essentially endorsed a second term for President Trump, who handily won the state’s electoral votes in 2016.

abstract: Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
headline_main: Can Bernie Be Stopped? Some Democratic Donors Are Trying

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.
snippet: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reu...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.
headline_main: Sanders Surpasses Biden Among African American Voters: Reuters/Ipsos Poll
headline_print_headline: Sanders Surpasses Biden Among African American Voters: Reuters/Ipsos Poll
